#22453
The Shrine of the Rose~
A soft rose-coloured light fills the area, shining down through the
tinted glass which makes up the domed ceiling of the shrine.  The small
panes above you are sectioned into the shape of a rose, and separated by
thin strips of pure silver.  The structure itself is constructed in a
circular shape, although only a curved wall at the north side, and two
silver pillars to the south hold up the encompassing roof.  Vines wrap their
way about the building, their growth apparently carefully tended.  Standing
at the middle of the northern wall is a tall silver statue of a beautiful
aelin woman atop an engraved pedestal, while in the middle of the shrine a
tiny fountain endlessly spurts a small stream of pure water.  A holy feeling
pervades the entire place, filling it with a sense of peacefulness.  
~
