statue~
Carved entirely of white marble, the statue depicts a young aelin woman,
her form remarkably delicate and feminine.  Her entire body flows and curves
fluidly, covered only by the graceful, sloping cover of a thin robe.

She is positioned with her back arched, her legs drawn back.  Her toes grow
firmly from the pedestal beneath, raising her body at a forward angle.
Behind her, two massive, perfectly detailed wings stretch skyward, drawn
wide, stylized similarly to that of an angel.  Long, lithe arms, uncovered,
extend out in front of her, angled downward, hands clasped around the hilt
of a beautifully crafted sword.  A thin and delicate rose entwines the
blade, the flower itself close to the girl\@s magnificently crafted fingers.

Her neck is also arched, lending her chin slightly up, her gaze skyward.
Her face is radiant and striking, crafted with extraordinary care to
maintain the tender smile glancing her lips.  Her hair drifts softly on a
static wind, flowing over the girl\@s pointed ears, showing painstaking
artisanship.  A rose rests over her left ear, strands of hair softly
cascading to either side of it.

On the pedestal, a small plaque reads:

                            For the Lord I Adore
                           Eternally in Your Care 
                      Yesa Aea\@ria, Archmagus of Waters
